shows several functions that are all related to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Color"},{"type":"text","text":" type."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME"},{"type":"text","text":" macro is applied to each function, giving each one a new name"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for Swift that’s nested together under the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Color"},{"type":"text","text":" type:"}]},{"code":["Color ColorCreateWithCMYK(float c, float m, float y, float k) CF_SWIFT_NAME(Color.init(c:m:y:k:));","","float ColorGetHue(Color color) CF_SWIFT_NAME(getter:Color.hue(self:));","void ColorSetHue(Color color, float hue) CF_SWIFT_NAME(setter:Color.hue(self:newValue:));","","Color ColorDarkenColor(Color color, float amount) CF_SWIFT_NAME(Color.darken(self:amount:));","","extern const Color ColorBondiBlue CF_SWIFT_NAME(Color.bondiBlue);","","Color ColorGetCalibrationColor(void) CF_SWIFT_NAME(getter:Color.calibration());","Color ColorSetCalibrationColor(Color color) CF_SWIFT_NAME(setter:Color.calibration(newValue:));"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"occ"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The argument you pass to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME"},{"type":"text","text":" macro uses the same syntax as the "},{"code":"#selector","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"expression. You use ","type":"text"},{"code":"self","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" argument to refer to the instance","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the method belongs to.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Import-Related-Functions-into-Swift","level":3,"text":"Import Related Functions into Swift","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here’s how Swift imports the related functions above into a single type:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Color {","    init(c: Float, m: Float, y: Float, k: Float)","","    var hue: Float { get set }","","    func darken(amount: Float) -> Color","","    static var bondiBlue: Color","","    static var calibration: Color","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can’t reorder or change the number of arguments for type members imported"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME"},{"type":"text","text":" macro."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift":{"role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how Swift represents imported C structures and unions, including types with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bitfields and unnamed fields."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift","title":"Using Imported C Structs and Unions in Swift","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift":{"role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use imported C-defined macros as constants."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift","title":"Using Imported C Macros in Swift","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to call imported functions that are declared in a C header."}],"title":"Using Imported C Functions in Swift","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift"}}}